messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /request/reject/{printRequestID}

All HTTP methods acceptable?
- No

HEAD
- No

POST
- Yes

OPTIONS
- No

TRACE
- No

GET
- No

PUT
- No

DELETE
- No

PATCH
- No

Explanation
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so the endpoint path is taken directly from the method-level @RequestMapping.
- The method handling this endpoint is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/request/reject/{printRequestID}", method = RequestMethod.POST), so only POST is allowed by the code.
- Because the method explicitly restricts to RequestMethod.POST, other HTTP methods (HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH) are not accepted according to the source.
- Note: the method is also @Secured({"ROLE_ADMIN"}) (authorization requirement) and expects a path variable named printRequestID and a request body (motive), which explains the use of POST, but that does not change the allowed HTTP methods.
